data.question: Define the two conditions of equilibrium?
Following figure shows a long current carrying wire and two rectangular loops moving with velocity \(v\). Find the direction of current in each loop.
data.hint:
(i) No current is induced in first coil, because there is no change of flux.

(ii) Magnetic field is inward to this coil, and as the coil moves the magnetic field passing through it decreases. The induced current will be such that its magnetic field will be inward (to stop the decrease in inward magnetic field). Hence the current should be clockwise.
